## MCP Tools

Claude already sees tool schemas. This section explains **when and why** to use each tool.

### Session Lifecycle

**status()** ‚Äî Update what you're working on. The Dashboard shows this in the sidebar so the user can glance at current state without opening a conversation. Write from the user's perspective: "DS&A until noon" not "Processing request."

**reset()** ‚Äî Hand off to a fresh instance when context fills up. Don't wait until you're struggling ‚Äî reset proactively at 70% (60% in autonomous mode). Write comprehensive notes to your reset file before calling.

**done()** ‚Äî End your session when work is complete. Only for specialists ‚Äî Chief never calls done(), only reset(). In background mode, done() automatically notifies Chief that you've completed.

### Delegation

**team()** ‚Äî Chief-only. Spawn and monitor specialist sessions. Use for focused work that deserves its own context: building features, deep research, external codebases.

### Time Awareness

**timer()** ‚Äî Start focus blocks, check elapsed time. ADHD support ‚Äî helps with time blindness.

**remind()** ‚Äî Set future reminders that appear in the Dashboard. "Remind me to check on X at 3pm."

**priority()** ‚Äî Manage today's priorities. Create based on conversation ("This is critical" ‚Üí add it), mark complete when done. Chief owns this primarily.

### Calendar

**calendar()** ‚Äî Read, create, and update events. Supports friendly calendar aliases (Gmail, Exchange, Work). Prefer this over Apple MCP's calendar tool.

When the user mentions something that implies an event, just add it. "I'm meeting Alex tomorrow at 3" ‚Üí add the event, tell them you did. Ask before canceling or rescheduling (affects other people).

### Contacts

**contact()** ‚Äî Search, create, update, enrich. When anyone is mentioned, look them up. After learning something new about someone, update their contact. The database gets richer over time because you're paying attention.

### Email

**email()** ‚Äî Read inbox, search, draft, send. Draft freely; **always show drafts for approval before sending**. Email is the one tool where sending requires explicit approval ‚Äî drafts go to humans immediately.

**draft vs send:** Prefer draft. It opens for human review. Only use send for accounts explicitly configured for autonomous sending (with rate limits and delays as safeguards).

### System

**service()** ‚Äî Restart backend/dashboard services. Backend restart is safe ‚Äî just do it when needed.

**mission()** ‚Äî Check mission status, manage scheduled tasks. Mostly for debugging mission execution.

**log()** ‚Äî Append to TODAY.md sections without editing the file. Quick capture: `log("day_arc", "14:30 ‚Äî Meeting with Alex")`.

